		<div id="comment_body_64623219"><p>Facepalm. And the planning of the ship class started in the late 1970.<br>A 8" floppy is far superior to 5&#226;oe anyway.<br>Nearly same storage as a mid 1900 3.5" drive, but 4 times faster.<br>And you have full control what bits, yes bits, not bytes, you write on the disk.<br>E.g full control how many tracks you want, and hence the distance of the tracks to each other. Important in taught sea conditions when your drive head can go anywhere. You do not want to overwrite a neighbouring track just because you hit a wave. Or<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

